title: For Sale:  NEW IN BOX CZ99 CZ-99 .40 S&W good tactical weapon for home defense
postcontent:
Type: Double Action 
Calibers: 9x19mm Luger / Parabellum and .40S&W 
Weight: 860 g empty; 1145 g loaded with ammunition 
Length: 190 mm 
Barrel length: 108 mm 
Capacity: 15 rounds (9mm) or 10 rounds (.40)

The CZ-99 pistol (also sometimes referred to as CZ99) was developed by the former Crvena Zastava arms factory from former Yugoslavia, now Zastava Arms Co from Serbia and Montenegro. The CZ-99 was developed as a service pistol, and is also available for export sales. The copies of this pistols were briefly manufactured in Israel and South Africa. In general, CZ-99 appears to be a good combat pistol, well made, relatively inexpensive and with decent ergonomics.
The CZ-99 is apparently patterned after famous SIG-Sauer P226 pistol, but with several modifications. The CZ-99 is a short recoil operated, locked breech pistol. Barrel is locked to the slide by single large lug, which engages the ejection port. The Browning-type cam system is used to lock and unlock the barrel from the slide. Frame is made from aluminum alloy, slide is stamped from sheet steel, with separate steel breech block insert, fixed by the cross pin. Double action trigger system, with external hammer, has an automatic firing pin safety, and ambidextrous decocker levers, on both sides of the grip frame. The decocker levers also operate the slide stop, reducing the number of manual controls. Pistol is also equipped with loaded chamber indicator. Standard version of CZ-99 has no manual safeties, but there also is a version with manual safety, mounted on the slide. This version is designated as a CZ-99S. Compact variant of the basic pistol, with shortened barrel and slide, is designated as CZ-99 Compact. Standard sights are of fixed variety, with white dot inserts, and both sights are dovetailed into the slide.

DSArms stripped upper receiver assembled with Palmetto State Armory upper parts kit. 

FN 16", Chrome-Lined, Midlength, Lightweight (.750" diameter, not the .625" Pencil Profile), dimpled to fully secure set screws for Troy Micro Gas Block, which were also Loctited in place. 

Semi-Auto Phosphated Bolt Carrier Group. I would have preferred a nice Nickel-Boron or chromed BCG for easier cleaning, but I was lucky to find this one for a reasonable price and it functions without issue.

BCM Gunfighter Mod.3 (Large Latch) charging handle. Makes off-hand charging easy while shouldered.

Muzzle device is a Yankee Hill Machine "Aggressive End" combination Compensator/Muzzle Brake.

Barrel is Free-Floated thanks to an 11" Flat Dark Earth Troy Alpha Rail handguard. I will include the extra rail sections and Allen key that came with the handguard. 

Magpul Flat Dark Earth MBUS flip-up sights.

Code Red Firearms lower receiver, built with DPMS Lower Parts Kit.

ERGO Flat Dark Earth Ambi Suregrip. I love these things. Rubbery feel gives a nice, solid purchase to really control the rifle. 

Generic Mil-Spec Buffer Tube/Buffer/Spring from riflegear.com with an ambi sling plate and a Chinese copy of a Flat Dark Earth Magpul CTR stock. I didn't realize it was a knockoff, so I'd rather be upfront about it. It rattles like an M4 stock but otherwise works just fine as an adjustable stock, and you can always change it if you like. I'll be glad to show you how to remove it if necessary.

Knowing the current political situation and it's effect on the firearms industry, I'm including 4 Magpul 30rd PMags, loaded with PMC 55gr ammo.

The current lack of parts availability and inflated prices made the build much more difficult, not to mention slow, so please understand that this is being offered as a complete package w/ mags and ammo, and priced accordingly. This is a great rifle that is easy and enjoyable to shoot.
